# Known divergence (by design): fast-path FunctionCall is explicitly rejected
# by the multigateway.
#
# PostgreSQL answers a fast-path FunctionCall ('F') with FunctionCallResponse.
# The multigateway rejects the message with a clean ErrorResponse (SQLSTATE
# 0A000, feature_not_supported) followed by ReadyForQuery, and keeps the
# session alive — a stray fast-path call degrades one command cycle instead of
# killing the connection. libpq's large-object API (psql \lo_*, pg_dump with
# blobs, JDBC LargeObjectManager) is the main remaining fast-path user;
# implementing passthrough is tracked as future work.
#
# This patch records the CURRENT (rejected) behaviour. If fast-path
# passthrough lands, the gateway will return FunctionCallResponse and match
# PostgreSQL, this patch will stop applying (a residual diff appears) and the
# suite will flag it — delete the patch then.
--- a
+++ b
@@ -1,2 +1,2 @@
-<= BE FunctionCallResponse
+<= BE ErrorResponse(C 0A000)
 <= BE ReadyForQuery(I)
